# Cross Tech Stack Spec Skill

Use this rule as an extension to `backend-service-spec-skill.mdc` when one of these is true:

- the user explicitly asks for cross-tech-stack analysis or mixed-stack mapping
- the target repository is primarily mobile, H5, web frontend, Python, data, worker, script, or mixed-stack
- the requested route crosses page, app, client, backend, task, callback, webhook, bridge, gateway, or message boundaries

Do not use this rule by default for ordinary backend-only microservice analysis. In that case, use `backend-service-spec-skill.mdc`.

## Required Skill Source

Before producing artifacts, read the skill source from one of these locations:

- If this skill library exists in the target project: `cross-tech-stack-spec-skill/SKILL.md`
- If copied under a shared skill folder: `skills/cross-tech-stack-spec-skill/SKILL.md`
- If cloned as a project-local rule source: `ai-skill-lib/cross-tech-stack-spec-skill/SKILL.md`
- Also read `backend-service-spec-skill/SKILL.md`, `skills/backend-service-spec-skill/SKILL.md`, or `ai-skill-lib/backend-service-spec-skill/SKILL.md` because this rule extends the backend service workflow instead of replacing it.

